<glossary>
<definition id="import-auto-id1773118"><term>Bernoulli’s equation</term> <meaning id="fs-id2928966">the equation resulting from applying conservation of energy to an incompressible frictionless fluid: <emphasis effect="italics">P</emphasis> + 1/2<emphasis effect="italics">pv</emphasis><sup>2</sup> + <emphasis effect="italics">pgh</emphasis> = constant , through the fluid</meaning></definition>
<definition id="import-auto-id1341325"><term>Bernoulli’s principle</term> <meaning id="fs-id2383369">Bernoulli’s equation applied at constant depth: <emphasis effect="italics">P</emphasis><sub>1</sub> + 1/2<emphasis effect="italics">pv</emphasis><sub>1</sub><sup>2</sup> = <emphasis effect="italics">P</emphasis><sub>2</sub> + 1/2<emphasis effect="italics">pv</emphasis><sub>2</sub><sup>2</sup></meaning></definition>
</glossary>
